Definition:
In this tasks you are given a tuple of two terms separated by "
". You have to determine whether the Second term is an event that happens as a subevent of the First term or not. Classify your answers as either "Yes" or "No".

Positive Examples.input:
First term: llearning to retain facts better 
Second term: committing to memory
Positive Examples.explanation: It is True since "llearning to retain facts better" is an event that happens as a subevent of "committing to memory".

Second term: examine thing
Positive Examples.explanation: It is False since "look at carefully" is typically not an event that happens as a subevent of "examine thing".

Negative Examples.input:
First term: use keyboard 
Second term: use computer
Negative Examples.explanation: It is False since "use keyboard" is typically not an event that happens as a subevent of "use computer". Hence, output "Yes" is incorrect.

Negative Examples.input:
First term: might fail 
Second term: take exam
Negative Examples.explanation: It is True since "might fail" is an event that happens as a subevent of "take exam". Hence, output "No" is incorrect.
